content:
Salesforce Data Pipelines use purpose built data templates for common use case data tasks to accelerate your ROI. These data templates generate the necessary data connectors, data prep recipes, and queries for apps that can be scheduled to run regularly.

Available in Salesforce Classic and Lightning Experience.
Available with CRM Analytics, which is available for an extra cost in Enterprise, Performance, and Unlimited Editions. Also available in Developer Edition.

To view, edit, or delete templated data assets: Analytics View Only Embedded App and Analytics View Only User

Data templates are ready-made data manipulation processes ready to be deployed in a matter of clicks. Theyâ€™re designed to do the heavy lifting for the most common data use cases so you can focus your attention on the results rather than the process.

Data Template Scenarios:

Scenario 1: Data Augmentation - Use a data template to generate data assets that combine CRM and HR data.
Scenario 2: Metric Calculations - Use a data template to calculate PipelinesCoverage from opportunity and quota data.
Scenario 3: Data Cleanup - Use a data template to import, clean, and output contact data to Salesforce.

Data templates have three levels of functionality:
Basic: Simple data editing and calculations
Intermediate: More advanced data manipulation
Advanced: Ready-made rigorous analysis

To create data assets from a data template, follow these procedures. Before you use a template, see the help for the Data Template that you want to use for requirements and instructions specific to that template.

Available Data Templates:
Simple data editing and calculations
Advanced data manipulation
Rigorous analysis
title: Accelerate ROI with Salesforce Data Templates
